research_municipality_step.notes: Houston, TX operates under a strong Mayor-Council form of government. The Mayor, City Controller, and 16 City Council members (11 district-based and 5 at-large) are elected for four-year terms. John Whitmire was sworn in as Mayor on January 2, 2024. Martha Castex-Tatum serves as Mayor Pro-Tem and Amy Peck as Vice Mayor Pro-Tem.
